This is an implementation of a collection of shaders from ShaderToy.com
employed as visualization addon of XBMC/Kodi.


Requirements:
 - OpenGLES
 - Kodi 14 or higher
 - sudo apt-get install kodi-addon-dev  (if not available in your repository, then add developer repository of kodi)
 - CMake 
 - sudo apt-get install zip (needed to build the addon zip file)

Build:
 
 :> mkdir build
 :> cmake ../ -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
 :> make addon

 You will now have a visualization.shadertoy.zip file in the main folder. Install this in Kodi from the System/Add-Ons menu.

Tested on:
 - NVIDIA Jetson TK1 
 - Odroid XU4

 
